comments.body: Why can't we use your new `listEquals` here?
This code runs in the Dart VM so it can't import dart:ui (which foundation does).
Not that it matters too much, but what does `hashAllUnordered` do here over hash all?

Order independent hashing. https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/commit/83376bf1ee81607a182f8558b242f1c9f4883246#diff-dc1389d26b294bb9804491e03fdf84c939c81eddc77578a0d90417b052f2a3c8R524

It's probably not super necessary here, where the map is always going to be a LinkedHashMap and preserve order, but I did it for the other map so I figured why not here too.
